# Pre-Release Review

Before cutting a release, run this review against all changed files since the last tag.

## 1. Correctness
- [ ] No dead code or unreachable branches
- [ ] No silently swallowed errors — log or return every `error`
- [ ] All function parameters are used (no dead params)
- [ ] Migrations are idempotent — running twice produces no diff
- [ ] Edge cases tested: empty input, nil maps, missing keys, invalid formats

## 2. Data Safety
- [ ] File writes don't destroy existing content (round-trip fidelity)
- [ ] String-replace migrations won't match unintended content
- [ ] No PII or secrets in logs, templates, or generated files

## 3. Tests
- [ ] Every exported function has at least one test
- [ ] Edge-case coverage: invalid input, boundary values, concurrent access
- [ ] Migration tests verify both in-memory state AND file-on-disk content
- [ ] Idempotency tests: run the operation twice, assert no change on second run

## 4. DRY / Clean Code
- [ ] No copy-paste logic — extract shared helpers
- [ ] No unnecessary type conversions (e.g. float64 round-trips for int math)
- [ ] Comments explain *why*, not *what*
- [ ] Docstrings on all exported types and functions

## 5. CI Gate
```bash
make ci   # tests + vet + lint must all pass
```
Only pre-existing lint violations are acceptable. New code must be lint-clean.

## 6. Docs
- [ ] CHANGELOG updated with all user-facing changes
- [ ] README reflects new config fields, CLI flags, and behaviors
